The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 September is 3,336 (386.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 September, there were 103 new confirmed cases (11.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 September, there were 127 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 19% (24 fewer cases).
